SEARCH

Class Parser

java.lang.Object
Parser
public class Parser extends Object
Parser class is a recursive descent LL(1) parser that parses a given input file according to its action table and its context-free grammar.

    • parseRecursive

      public boolean parseRecursive(ContextFreeGrammar contextFreeGrammar, String[][] actionTable, List<Symbol> inputWord, Stack<Symbol> stack, int j)
      Parses the input and prints the leftmost derivation of the given input word.
      Parameters:
      contextFreeGrammar - An LL(1) Context-Free Grammar.
      actionTable - The action table of the Context-Free Grammar.
      inputWord - The input word to be parsed.
      stack - The stack used in the parsing process.
      j - The index pointing to the current symbol in the input word.
      Returns:
      True if the input word is a valid part of the grammar and prints the leftmost derivation on stdout. False if the input word is not part of the grammar, and an explanatory error is thrown.

      Parameters:

      actionTable - The action table of the Context-Free Grammar.
      inputWord - The input word to be parsed.
      Returns:
      True if the input word is a valid part of the grammar. False if the input word is not part of the grammar.
